4.01	Asa_Grant_Hilliard_III	Asa Grant Hilliard III	Asa G. Hilliard III (August 22, 1933 â€” August 13, 2007) was an African American professor of educational psychology who worked on indigenous ancient African history (ancient Egyptian), culture, education and society. He was the Fuller E. Callaway Professor of Urban Education at Georgia State University, with joint appointments in the Department of Educational Policy Studies and the Department of Educational Psychology and Special Education.	
